</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1580745755767_9987"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><br>Each Octoprint instance will be bound only to 127.0.0.1 and use different ports to bind to.  This will make sure that there’s no insecure access to the Octoprint software, and haproxy will do the mapping from the network IPs to the local ports.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Here’s a functional diagram that helps show how we’ll use haproxy and udev to publish multiple instances:</p></div></div><div class="sqs-block image-block sqs-block-image" data-block-type="5" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1580745755767_13025"><div class="sqs-block-content">















  

    
  
