</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1581174777410_133468"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">It wouldn’t be a back7 post without a cool photo, so here’s one of my production Pi.  I’m using a simple metal case to keep it safe, but I also have Bluetooth and WiFi disabled.  I’m running the entire Pi off a Power-over-Ethernet (PoE) Raspberry Pi hat, so I don’t even need a power plug for the Pi.  My PoE network switch has a battery backup as well.  </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Parts are listed below for reference:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Raspberry Pi PoE Adapter -<a href="https://amzn.to/2H7e3Qm"> Amazon</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Raspberry Pi 4 - <a href="https://amzn.to/31H6DNk">Amazon</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Metal Raspberry Pi Enclosure - <a href="https://amzn.to/2SaPR68">Amazon</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">This PoE 4-Port Network Switch (<a href="https://amzn.to/2H39yGq">Amazon</a>) or this Ubiquiti one (<a href="https://amzn.to/2SdRLCZ">Amazon</a>)</p></li></ul><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">References:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://octoprint.org/">The Amazing Octoprint software</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://www.endpoint.com/blog/2014/10/30/openssl-csr-with-alternative-names-one">Generate an OpenSSL CSR with one line</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://blog.taragana.com/guide-haproxy-http-basic-authentication-for-specific-sites-ssl-termination-15813">Forcing haproxy authentication for specific sites</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://gist.github.com/cecilemuller/9492b848eb8fe46d462abeb26656c4f8">Creating local HTTPS certificates</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27947982/haproxy-unable-to-load-ssl-private-key-from-pem-file">Merge a crt and key file to make a .pem (in the comments)</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://gist.github.com/Soarez/9688998">Setup your own CA with OpenSSL</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://medium.com/@tbusser/creating-a-browser-trusted-self-signed-ssl-certificate-2709ce43fd15">Creating Self Signed Certificates</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="http://www.prusamk2.com/using-multiple-3d-printers-single-raspberry-pi-octoprint/">Using multiple 3D printers with Octoprint</a> (-10 points for the javascript that prevents copying code though)</p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://docs.octoprint.org/en/master/configuration/config_yaml.html#feature">Octoprint config reference</a> &amp; <a href="https://github.com/foosel/OctoPrint/wiki/Configuration">here too</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://blog.sleeplessbeastie.eu/2018/03/08/how-to-define-basic-authentication-on-haproxy/">Basic Authentication in HAProxy</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43323953/how-to-set-multiple-ip-address-on-a-raspberry-pi-3">Setting multiple IP addresses on a Raspberry Pi</a></p></li><li><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://octoprint.org/blog/2018/09/03/safe-remote-access/">Safe remote access for Octoprint</a></p></li></ul><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Thanks for reading along!  I hope you find it useful- please reach out to me if this helps you.  </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><br><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div>

        <footer class="blog-item-footer">

